Package: cruise-control
Version: 1.1.0
Architecture: arm64
Maintainer: Tim McGlothi <timmcg@gmail.com>
Depends: python3, python3-flask, iproute2
Recommends: kmod
Description: GB10 inbound bandwidth throttle web GUI
 Cruise Control is a web-based interface for rate-limiting inbound
 (download) network traffic on GB10-class machines. Uses Linux tc
 with IFB to shape ingress traffic. Useful for throttling model
 downloads during business hours or high-demand windows.
 .
 Features:
  - Live inbound/outbound speed display
  - Named presets with editable rates (saved across restarts)
  - Custom preset add/delete
  - Built-in speed test to validate settings
  - Systemd service (auto-start on boot)
Homepage: https://github.com/mcglothi/cruise-control
